variables.value: You ready for the dance battle?
Getting cold feet, <FLC:UNMEI>?\nYou're the one who picked this fight!
Gosh, I'm so hyped!\nI finally get to see Raika bust her moves again!
Today's another beautiful spring day...\nBut why lend an ear to a babbling brook like me?
People say I've got a big mouth.\nBut, hey, I always ride the talk, bro!
If you want my rock,\nI'll give it to you loud and clear.
I saw <FLC:SHUNTA> out walking one evening.
And get this—he was chatting all sweet with some old lady!\nNo way... Is he into older women? Maybe I should try a more mature look...
Dang it! Our youth's on pause\n'cause of you football punks?!
Don't forget! <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> hoops—\nfighting for fame and love!
...I see. I understand your point.\nBefore we can join hands with aliens,\nwe must first join hands with one another.
Since you're the one proposing this idea,\nI'd like to have a deep discussion about space with you.
To us, space is Eden—\na place humanity must one day reach.\nBut you're saying just admiring it... is love too?
You're the one who had that scuffle on the grounds, right?\nHardly any teachers come up here—It's a good place to clear your head.
That dance-off with <FST:RAIKA>... must've taken a ton of prep, huh?
The stargazing club comes up to actually watch the stars.\nThe space laboratory's here too...\nTrying to summon UFOs, apparently.
<FST:RAIKA>'s been glowing ever since she joined the football club.\nHonestly, I'm happy for her too.
Looks like some Northbright kids wandered over to our side.\nSee that group over there?
The northern building used to be the high school wing,\nso I never dared go near it. But now that it's Northbright's,\nmaybe I'll take a peek.
<FST:KAMEO>'s been looking way happier with the football club lately.\nHe used to eat lunch here all alone, so it's nice seeing him smile.
Sounds like the football club's made it to the finals.\nI always hear them practicing from up here...\nI think they've really got a shot.
I did a bit of digging online the other day...\nTurns out you used to play football, huh.
That showdown... it's really happening?\n...I-I just don't want them to lose, that's all!
Truth is... I've always dreamed of seeing a match\nat Football Frontier Stadium.
Surreal, huh...\nTalking about football at school like it's totally normal.
Didn't think a brand-new team could win their first match.\nThey've got a bunch of rookies too! Now that's impressive!
Northbright's got two real aces—<LST:SORAMIYA> and <FLC:SHINANO>.\nJust having them on the team makes a huge difference.
I saw someone who looked like <FUL:HARU> the other day.\nIf it had actually been him, I'd have asked for a signature,\nbut there's no way he's in <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.
I can't believe <FUL:SOJI> busted out a Keshin.\nIt's been ages since I last saw one... I got chills!
Guess what?! I get to go see your match live!\nAt the one and only Football Frontier Stadium...\nthis is the best day ever!
Sorry, I do want to join a club, but football's a bit much...\nI'm trying to keep my grades up, not draw the teachers' attention.
I'm thinking of joining the stargazing club.\nThe advisor's supposed to be nice,\nthough the club leader, <FLC:IIBA>, is kind of intimidating...
If I'd known it would get this tough,\nI would've joined football earlier!\nThe competition is so fierce, now.
I was curious about the karuta club, but not anymore.\nEven my idol, <FLC:GARYU>, is mostly into football now.
I'll make it happen,\nno matter what!
I'm putting my hopes\nin you, too...
They say we have to\nobey the adults.
I'm collecting signatures to get the Hecaton Stairway\nreplaced with escalators. I'll do whatever it takes\nto make getting to school easier.
The baseball club parents have a lot of sway\nwith school management. Best to keep them on our side.
Rumor has it <FLC:BANME>'s hands shake when he's nervous.\nSuch a shame... he's got incredible focus and sharp instincts.
If you'd told me a few months ago the whole school\nwould catch football fever, I'd never have believed it.
Even the rooftop garden is kept spotless\nthanks to the Cleanup Committee. If only they put that much care\ninto their own appearance...
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> is full of greenery, especially the rooftop garden.\nThat's why I keep coming back.
That robot you use for football practice...\nDoes it run on solar power, by any chance?
The big overhaul of the schoolyard was surprising,\nbut that fresh grass really makes it look better.
So Northbright students came over...\ndo you think they'll join the committees too?\nThe Cleanup Committee needs more members.
This rooftop garden's palms give it a nice tropical feel.\nThe colorful flowers are so beautiful I could look at them forever.
I hear the Football Gardens are full of greenery. Knowing only\nstaff and players can get in makes me even more curious.
I saw pictures of the team's lodging cottages. Holding\nstrategy meetings surrounded by nature sounds kinda amazing.
Can't find places like\nthis in public schools.
I did try to stop them,\nyou know.
Start a cheer squad\nfor the football club?
Let's get the old\ncrew to join too!
I'll find a way\nto film it.
Who knew <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> Junior High had a spot like this?\nThe stairs were brutal, but the trip was totally worth it!
I've been all over campus and it's huge!\nNorthbright's buildings looked nice, but <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> has way better facilities.
I was goofing off here the other day and almost fell in the water!\nAnyone else from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> ever had a close call like that?
We're gonna stream the finals here and cheer together.\nJust need to ask the teacher about using the rooftop.
Think this spot's\ngot a good view?
